apt-get install xvfb
sudo chmod u+s `which Xvfb`

sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install Data::GUID'
sudo perl -MCPAN -e 'install JSON::XS'

sudo apt-get install firefox

adduser fireshark
passwd fireshark <- create password for fireshark user
copy home stuff to fireshark dir
sudo su fireshark

type firefox which will fail but create default directories

create a bunch of ff profiles
/home/fireshark/m

manageffprofiles.pl -c 500

unzip extension to /usr/lib/firefox-addons/extensions/fireshark@fireshark.org

sudo update-rc.d fireshark defaults

copy over the otehr two .py files that are needed.

sudo chmod 755 -R /home/fireshark/.mozilla/
have to do above to make profiles writable

then add fireshark to sudo file (not sure but have to do this)

